comment: Thomas (NYK) and Lowry (TOR) make incidental contact with each other away from the ball.
RHH shows that Thomas (NYK) is retreating and maintains legal guarding position as he defends Lowry's (TOR) drive and shot attempt.
Lopez (NYK) jumps vertically while contesting Lowry's (TOR) driving shot attempt. The arm contact made on the play is incidental and is initiated by Lowry as the players land after the shot.
Valanciunas (TOR) sets the screen on Galloway (NYK) and gives him the opportunity to avoid the contact.
[Observable in enhanced video] Lowry (TOR) does not drag his pivot foot after ending his dribble.
Lopez (NYK) jumps and turns sideways and delivers body contact with Johnson (TOR) that affects his layup attempt.
Lowry (TOR) commits a take foul on Anthony (NYK).
After catching the inbound pass, Anthony (NYK) slides his pivot foot (left foot) while taking a step forward.
Anthony (NYK) steps out of bounds on the sideline with his right foot.
Lowry (TOR) commits a take foul on Thomas (TOR).
Valanciunas (TOR) sets the screen on Thomas (NYK) and gives him the opportunity to avoid the contact.
Lopez (NYK) makes contact with DeRozan's (TOR) arm that affects his driving layup attempt.
O'Quinn (NYK) and Valanciunas (TOR) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
Valanciunas (TOR) sets the screen on Thomas (NYK) and gives him the opportunity to avoid the contact.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by New York was upheld and Toronto was awarded possession.
O'Quinn (NYK) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with his left hand as he defends DeRozan's (TOR) driving layup attempt.
Lowry (TOR) grabs Thomas' (NYK) arm as he secures the loose ball.
Lowry (TOR) commits a take foul on Galloway (NYK).
